Description: Fragment of lip, neck and round handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Soteridas. From the same die as an example from Crocodilopolis, KF544.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0769)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (probably)
